						<summary>

						<p>MADRAS.</p>						

						<p>On a stone set up at the entrance into the Government Museum building.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">••• •••• Year 2, Mārgaḻi.</hi></p>						

						<p>Same as 295 of 1895. Published in S.I.I, V. Nos. 859.<note n="522-1">In the published text lines 10-12 have not been properly read. The lines actually read: 10. <ta>ḻimāta mutal tirunīrmalai</ta> 11. <ta>nāyaṉār nir[va]ṇa</ta> 12 <ta>ṇapperu</ta> The record seems to continue to line 21 on the phase, which contains the published text and also on another phase of the stone. But the writing is very much damaṅed and nothing coṅent can be made out.</note></p>						

						</summary>
